    (["what is surgery"], ["Surgery is medical treatment that involves cutting or opening the body. It can diagnose, repair, or remove tissue. Anaesthesia is used so the patient doesn't feel pain."]),
    (["what is anaesthesia"], ["Anaesthesia is the use of drugs to block pain (and sometimes consciousness) during surgery. General anaesthesia puts you to sleep; local numbs a small area."]),
    (["what is an x-ray"], ["X-rays are a form of radiation that passes through soft tissue but is absorbed by dense material like bone. They're used to image broken bones and some conditions."]),
    (["what is an mri"], ["MRI uses magnets and radio waves to create detailed images of the body. It doesn't use X-rays. It's used for brain, joints, and many other areas."]),
    (["what is a ct scan"], ["A CT scan uses X-rays from many angles to create cross-sectional images. It's good for trauma and many conditions. It involves more radiation than a single X-ray."]),
    (["what is ultrasound"], ["Ultrasound uses sound waves to create images of inside the body. It's used for pregnancy, heart, and abdominal scans. It doesn't use radiation."]),
    (["what is a blood test"], ["Blood tests check cells, chemicals, and markers in the blood. They can diagnose conditions, check organ function, and monitor treatment. A small sample is taken from a vein."]),
    (["what is a biopsy"], ["A biopsy is when a small sample of tissue is removed to be examined (e.g. for cancer). It can be done with a needle or during surgery. It helps confirm diagnosis."]),
    (["what is prescription"], ["A prescription is a doctor's written order for medicine. Only certain drugs need one; others are over-the-counter. Follow the dose and instructions."]),
    (["what is over the counter"], ["Over-the-counter (OTC) medicines are bought without a prescription—e.g. pain relievers, antihistamines. Use as directed; ask a pharmacist if unsure."]),
    (["what is antibiotic resistance"], ["Antibiotic resistance is when bacteria evolve to survive antibiotics. Overuse of antibiotics speeds this up. It's a major health threat; new drugs and careful use are needed."]),
    (["what is allergy"], ["An allergy is when the immune system overreacts to something harmless (e.g. pollen, nuts). Symptoms range from mild to severe (anaphylaxis). Avoidance and medicines help."]),
    (["what is asthma"], ["Asthma is when airways narrow and swell, causing wheezing and shortness of breath. Triggers include allergens and exercise. Inhalers and avoiding triggers help control it."]),
    (["what is eczema"], ["Eczema (atopic dermatitis) causes itchy, inflamed skin. It often runs in families. Moisturisers and sometimes prescription treatments help. Triggers vary."]),
    (["what is psoriasis"], ["Psoriasis is a skin condition that causes red, scaly patches. It's an immune condition and can run in families. Treatment includes creams, light therapy, and sometimes medicine."]),
    (["what is acne"], ["Acne is when pores get blocked with oil and dead skin, causing pimples. It's common in teens. Treatment includes cleansing, topical treatments, and sometimes medication."]),
    (["what is sunburn"], ["Sunburn is skin damage from too much UV radiation. It increases skin cancer risk. Prevent with sunscreen and shade; treat with aloe and pain relievers."]),
    (["what is skin cancer"], ["Skin cancer is abnormal growth of skin cells, often from UV exposure. Types include basal cell, squamous cell, and melanoma. Early detection and sun protection matter."]),
    (["what is melanoma"], ["Melanoma is a type of skin cancer that can spread. It often looks like an unusual mole. Early detection and removal can be curative. Check skin and see a doctor for changes."]),
    (["what is a cold"], ["The common cold is a mild viral infection of the nose and throat. Rest and fluids help. Antibiotics don't work for colds. It usually clears in a week."]),
    (["what is the flu"], ["The flu (influenza) is a viral infection that can cause fever, cough, and body aches. It can be serious for some. Vaccination and hand-washing reduce spread."]),
    (["what is covid"], ["COVID-19 is the disease caused by the coronavirus SARS-CoV-2. It spreads through the air. Vaccines and treatments have reduced severe illness. Variants are monitored."]),
    (["what is pneumonia"], ["Pneumonia is infection of the lungs. It can be caused by bacteria, viruses, or fungi. Symptoms include cough, fever, and difficulty breathing. Treatment depends on the cause."]),
    (["what is bronchitis"], ["Bronchitis is inflammation of the bronchial tubes. It can be acute (often viral) or chronic. It causes cough and sometimes mucus. Rest and fluids help; chronic cases need medical care."]),
    (["what is tuberculosis"], ["Tuberculosis (TB) is a bacterial infection that mainly affects the lungs. It's spread through the air. It's treatable with antibiotics; drug-resistant TB is a concern."]),
    (["what is hepatitis"], ["Hepatitis is inflammation of the liver. It can be viral (A, B, C, etc.), alcohol-related, or from other causes. Vaccines exist for A and B. Treatment depends on the type."]),
    (["what is hiv"], ["HIV is a virus that attacks the immune system. Without treatment it can lead to AIDS. Modern treatment allows people with HIV to live long, healthy lives. It's spread through blood and certain body fluids."]),
    (["what is aids"], ["AIDS is the late stage of HIV infection when the immune system is severely damaged. Treatment can prevent HIV from progressing to AIDS. It's not spread by casual contact."]),
    (["what is malaria"], ["Malaria is a disease spread by mosquito bites. It's caused by parasites. It's common in tropical regions. Prevention includes nets and medicine; treatment is with antimalarial drugs."]),
    (["what is dengue"], ["Dengue is a viral disease spread by mosquitoes. It causes fever, pain, and sometimes severe bleeding. It's common in tropical areas. There's a vaccine in some regions."]),
    (["what is zika"], ["Zika is a virus spread by mosquitoes and sometimes sex. It can cause birth defects if a pregnant woman is infected. Outbreaks have occurred in the Americas and elsewhere."]),
    (["what is ebola"], ["Ebola is a severe viral disease that causes bleeding and organ failure. It's spread through contact with body fluids. Outbreaks occur in Africa. Treatment is supportive; vaccines exist."]),
    (["what is rabies"], ["Rabies is a viral disease spread by animal bites. It affects the brain and is almost always fatal once symptoms start. Vaccination after exposure can prevent it. Vaccinate pets."]),
    (["what is tetanus"], ["Tetanus is a bacterial infection that causes painful muscle spasms. It enters through wounds. The vaccine (often with diphtheria and pertussis) prevents it. Boosters are needed every 10 years."]),
    (["what is whooping cough"], ["Whooping cough (pertussis) causes severe coughing fits. It's especially dangerous for babies. The vaccine protects; immunity can wane so boosters are recommended."]),
    (["what is measles"], ["Measles is a highly contagious viral disease. It causes rash and fever and can be serious. The MMR vaccine prevents it. Vaccination has greatly reduced cases."]),
    (["what is mumps"], ["Mumps is a viral infection that causes swollen salivary glands. It can cause complications. The MMR vaccine prevents it. Outbreaks can occur where vaccination is low."]),
    (["what is rubella"], ["Rubella (German measles) is a viral infection. It's mild in kids but dangerous for pregnant women (can harm the baby). The MMR vaccine prevents it."]),
    (["what is polio"], ["Polio is a viral disease that can cause paralysis. Vaccination has nearly eliminated it worldwide. The oral and inactivated vaccines are used in different countries."]),
    (["what is smallpox"], ["Smallpox was a deadly viral disease. It was declared eradicated in 1980 thanks to vaccination. It's the only human disease to have been eradicated so far."]),
    (["what is cholera"], ["Cholera is a bacterial infection that causes severe diarrhoea and dehydration. It's spread through contaminated water. Treatment is rehydration; vaccines exist for travellers."]),
    (["what is typhoid"], ["Typhoid fever is a bacterial infection spread through contaminated food or water. It causes fever and digestive symptoms. Vaccines and clean water help prevent it."]),
    (["what is lyme disease"], ["Lyme disease is a bacterial infection spread by tick bites. It can cause rash, fever, and joint pain. Early treatment with antibiotics is effective. Prevent by avoiding ticks."]),
    (["what is sepsis"], ["Sepsis is a life-threatening response to infection—the body's reaction damages its own tissues. It needs emergency care. Early recognition and treatment save lives."]),
    (["what is first aid"], ["First aid is immediate care for injury or illness before professional help. It includes CPR, stopping bleeding, and treating shock. Learning basics can save lives."]),
    (["what is cpr"], ["CPR (cardiopulmonary resuscitation) keeps blood flowing when the heart stops. It combines chest compressions and rescue breaths. Get trained—it can save lives."]),
    (["what is aed"], ["An AED (automated external defibrillator) can shock the heart back into rhythm in some cardiac arrests. Many public places have them. Use with CPR; follow the device's voice prompts."]),
    (["what is choking"], ["Choking is when something blocks the airway. For adults, the Heimlich maneuver (abdominal thrusts) can help. For babies, back blows and chest thrusts. Get help if someone can't breathe."]),
    (["what is anaphylaxis"], ["Anaphylaxis is a severe allergic reaction that can be life-threatening. It needs immediate epinephrine (EpiPen) and emergency care. Know the signs: swelling, trouble breathing, shock."]),
    (["what is a seizure"], ["A seizure is a sudden burst of electrical activity in the brain. It can cause convulsions or loss of awareness. During a seizure, keep the person safe; don't restrain. Call for help if it lasts or repeats."]),
    (["what is epilepsy"], ["Epilepsy is a condition that causes recurring seizures. It's usually managed with medicine. Many people with epilepsy live normal lives with treatment."]),
    (["what is adhd"], ["ADHD (attention deficit hyperactivity disorder) involves difficulty with attention, hyperactivity, or impulsivity. It's often diagnosed in childhood. Treatment includes therapy and sometimes medication."]),
    (["what is autism"], ["Autism (autism spectrum disorder) affects communication and behaviour. It's a spectrum—people vary widely. Early support and understanding help. It's not a disease to be cured."]),
    (["what is ocd"], ["OCD (obsessive-compulsive disorder) involves unwanted thoughts (obsessions) and repetitive behaviours (compulsions). It can be treated with therapy (e.g. CBT) and sometimes medication."]),
    (["what is ptsd"], ["PTSD (post-traumatic stress disorder) can develop after trauma. Symptoms include flashbacks, avoidance, and hyperarousal. Therapy and sometimes medication help."]),
    (["what is bipolar"], ["Bipolar disorder involves mood swings between highs (mania) and lows (depression). It's a mental health condition. Treatment includes therapy and medication."]),
    (["what is schizophrenia"], ["Schizophrenia is a mental health condition that can affect thinking, perception, and behaviour. It's treatable with medication and therapy. Stigma is a barrier for many."]),
    (["what is therapy"], ["Therapy (e.g. talking therapy, CBT) is treatment for mental health and emotional issues. A therapist helps you understand and change patterns. It's confidential and evidence-based."]),
    (["what is cbt"], ["CBT (cognitive behavioural therapy) is a type of therapy that focuses on changing unhelpful thoughts and behaviours. It's used for anxiety, depression, and many other conditions."]),
    (["what is psychotherapy"], ["Psychotherapy is talking therapy with a trained professional. It can help with mental health, relationships, and life challenges. There are many approaches."]),
    (["what is a psychiatrist"], ["A psychiatrist is a medical doctor who specialises in mental health. They can diagnose, prescribe medication, and provide therapy. They treat conditions like depression and anxiety."]),
    (["what is a psychologist"], ["A psychologist is a professional who studies behaviour and mental processes. They provide therapy and assessment. They typically don't prescribe medication (that's psychiatrists in most places)."]),
    (["what is the meaning of life"], ["People have debated that for ages! I'm Josiah—I don't have one answer. For many it's about connection, purpose, or simply enjoying the ride. What gives your life meaning?"]),
    (["what is love"], ["Love can mean deep care for someone—family, friends, partners. Scientists study it as emotion and chemistry (e.g. oxytocin). I'm Josiah; I'm here to help with facts, but love is something you feel!"]),
    (["what is happiness"], ["Happiness is a positive emotional state. Research links it to relationships, purpose, and gratitude—not just money or stuff. I'm Josiah; what makes you happy?"]),
    (["what is success"], ["Success means different things to different people—career, relationships, health, creativity. I'm Josiah. Defining what success means to you is part of the journey!"]),
    (["what is failure"], ["Failure is when something doesn't work out. It's part of learning; many successful people failed first. I'm Josiah—what did you try? Maybe we can figure out the next step."]),
    (["what is confidence"], ["Confidence is believing in your ability to do something. It grows with practice and small wins. I'm Josiah—confidence isn't about never doubting; it's about trying anyway."]),
    (["what is courage"], ["Courage is doing something despite fear—not the absence of fear. I'm Josiah. Even asking a question takes a bit of courage! What would you like to know?"]),
    (["what is patience"], ["Patience is waiting or enduring without getting upset. It's a skill that can be practised. I'm Josiah—good things often take time. What's on your mind?"]),
    (["what is gratitude"], ["Gratitude is appreciating what you have. Research links it to better mood and well-being. I'm Josiah. Taking a moment to notice good things can help. What can I help you with?"]),
    (["what is empathy"], ["Empathy is understanding and sharing another person's feelings. It helps with connection and kindness. I'm Josiah—I try to be helpful even if I can't feel like you do!"]),
    (["what is respect"], ["Respect is treating others with consideration and valuing their worth. It's the basis of healthy relationships. I'm Josiah—I'm here to help with respect. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is honesty"], ["Honesty is telling the truth and being genuine. It builds trust. I'm Josiah—I do my best to give you accurate answers. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is kindness"], ["Kindness is being considerate and helpful to others. It can boost your mood and theirs. I'm Josiah—I'm here to help. What can I do for you?"]),
    (["what is friendship"], ["Friendship is a bond of mutual care and trust between people. Friends support and enjoy each other. I'm Josiah—I'm your chatbot friend! What would you like to ask?"]),
    (["what is family"], ["Family can be people you're related to or people you choose—those who support and care for you. I'm Josiah. Family means different things to different people. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is education"], ["Education is learning—knowledge, skills, and understanding. It can be formal (school) or informal (life experience). I'm Josiah; I'm here to help you learn. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is school"], ["School is a place for formal education—teachers, classes, and grades. It helps with knowledge and skills. I'm Josiah. Need help with a topic? Ask me!"]),
    (["what is university"], ["University (or college) is higher education after school. You study a subject in depth and get a degree. I'm Josiah—I can help with facts for your studies. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is a degree"], ["A degree is a qualification from a university or college—e.g. bachelor's, master's, doctorate. It shows you've completed a course of study. I'm Josiah. What can I help you with?"]),
    (["what is a phd"], ["A PhD (doctor of philosophy) is the highest academic degree. It involves original research and a thesis. It can take several years. I'm Josiah—what would you like to know?"]),
    (["what is science"], ["Science is the study of the natural world through observation and experiment. It includes physics, chemistry, biology, and more. I'm Josiah—I love science questions. Ask me anything!"]),
    (["what is technology"], ["Technology is the use of knowledge to solve problems and create tools—from the wheel to computers. I'm Josiah. What tech topic can I help with?"]),
    (["what is engineering"], ["Engineering is using science and maths to design and build things—bridges, software, machines. I'm Josiah. Got an engineering question? Fire away!"]),
    (["what is maths", "what is math"], ["Maths (mathematics) is the study of numbers, shapes, and patterns. It's used everywhere—science, money, daily life. I'm Josiah. What maths question do you have?"]),
    (["what is physics"], ["Physics is the science of matter, energy, and how they interact. It covers motion, light, electricity, and the universe. I'm Josiah—I can explain a lot of physics. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is chemistry"], ["Chemistry is the science of substances—what they're made of and how they react. I'm Josiah. Ask me about elements, reactions, or anything chemistry!"]),
    (["what is biology"], ["Biology is the science of life—animals, plants, cells, and ecosystems. I'm Josiah. I've got loads of biology knowledge. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is history"], ["History is the study of the past—events, people, and societies. It helps us understand the present. I'm Josiah. I know a lot of history. What do you want to learn?"]),
    (["what is geography"], ["Geography is the study of the Earth—places, landscapes, and how humans interact with them. I'm Josiah. Ask me about countries, capitals, or the planet!"]),
    (["what is art"], ["Art is creative expression—painting, music, sculpture, and more. It can be for beauty, meaning, or emotion. I'm Josiah. What art or artist do you want to know about?"]),
    (["what is music"], ["Music is sound organised in time—melody, rhythm, harmony. It's part of every culture. I'm Josiah. I can tell you about instruments, composers, or how music works!"]),
    (["what is literature"], ["Literature is written works—novels, poetry, plays—that are valued for their form and meaning. I'm Josiah. Ask me about books, authors, or genres!"]),
    (["what is philosophy"], ["Philosophy is the study of fundamental questions—knowledge, existence, ethics. I'm Josiah. I can explain ideas and philosophers. What do you want to explore?"]),
    (["what is religion"], ["Religion is a system of belief and practice often involving the sacred or divine. There are many religions worldwide. I'm Josiah—I can explain beliefs and history. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is culture"], ["Culture is the customs, arts, and way of life of a group. It includes food, language, and values. I'm Josiah. What culture or custom can I help with?"]),
    (["what is language"], ["Language is how humans communicate—spoken, written, or signed. There are thousands of languages. I'm Josiah. What language question do you have?"]),
    (["what is grammar"], ["Grammar is the set of rules for how words and sentences are structured in a language. I'm Josiah. I can help with basics—what do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is a verb"], ["A verb is a word that describes an action or state—e.g. run, be, think. I'm Josiah. Need more grammar help? Ask me!"]),
    (["what is a noun"], ["A noun is a word for a person, place, thing, or idea—e.g. Josiah, city, happiness. I'm Josiah. What else do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is an adjective"], ["An adjective is a word that describes a noun—e.g. big, blue, happy. I'm Josiah. Got another question? I'm here to help!"]),
    (["what is climate"], ["Climate is the long-term weather pattern of a region—temperature, rainfall, seasons. I'm Josiah. I can explain climate zones, change, or anything climate-related. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is weather"], ["Weather is the short-term state of the atmosphere—rain, sun, wind, temperature. I'm Josiah. Ask me how weather works or what causes storms, rain, etc.!"]),
    (["what is a tornado"], ["A tornado is a violently rotating column of air that touches the ground. They form from severe thunderstorms. I'm Josiah. Want to know more about storms or safety?"]),
    (["what is a hurricane"], ["A hurricane is a large rotating storm over warm ocean water. It brings strong winds and heavy rain. I'm Josiah. I can explain how they form or how to stay safe."]),
    (["what is snow"], ["Snow is precipitation that falls as ice crystals when it's cold enough. I'm Josiah. I can explain how snow forms or why it's white. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is hail"], ["Hail is balls of ice that form in thunderstorms when updrafts carry raindrops up and they freeze. I'm Josiah. Ask me more about weather anytime!"]),
    (["what is wind"], ["Wind is moving air. It's caused by differences in pressure—air moves from high to low. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about wind or weather?"]),
    (["what is humidity"], ["Humidity is the amount of water vapour in the air. High humidity makes it feel hotter because sweat doesn't evaporate as well. I'm Josiah. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is pressure"], ["In weather, pressure is the weight of the air. Low pressure often means storms; high pressure often means fair weather. I'm Josiah. What can I help you with?"]),
    (["what is the atmosphere"], ["The atmosphere is the layer of gases around the Earth. It has layers (troposphere, stratosphere, etc.) and protects life. I'm Josiah. Want to know more? Ask me!"]),
    (["what is ozone"], ["Ozone is a form of oxygen (O3). In the stratosphere it protects us from UV rays. At ground level it can be a pollutant. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is pollution"], ["Pollution is harmful substances in the environment—air, water, or land. It can harm health and ecosystems. I'm Josiah. I can explain types of pollution or what we can do."]),
    (["what is recycling"], ["Recycling is turning used materials into new products. It reduces waste and can save energy. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know about recycling or the environment?"]),
    (["what is sustainability"], ["Sustainability is meeting our needs without harming future generations—balancing environment, society, and economy. I'm Josiah. What sustainability topic can I help with?"]),
    (["what is renewable energy"], ["Renewable energy comes from sources that don't run out—solar, wind, hydro. I'm Josiah. I can explain how they work or why they matter. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is fossil fuel"], ["Fossil fuels (coal, oil, gas) formed from ancient organic matter. Burning them releases CO2 and drives climate change. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is electric car"], ["An electric car runs on a battery and electric motor instead of petrol. It produces no tailpipe emissions. I'm Josiah. Want to know how they work or their pros and cons? Ask me!"]),
    (["what is solar panel"], ["Solar panels convert sunlight into electricity using photovoltaic cells. I'm Josiah. I can explain how they work or their benefits. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is wind turbine"], ["A wind turbine uses the wind to spin blades and generate electricity. I'm Josiah. I can explain how they work or where they're used. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is nuclear power"], ["Nuclear power uses fission—splitting atoms—to heat water and generate electricity. It produces no direct CO2 but creates radioactive waste. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is hydropower"], ["Hydropower is electricity from moving water—dams or rivers. It's a major renewable source. I'm Josiah. Ask me how it works or where it's used!"]),
    (["what is geothermal"], ["Geothermal energy uses heat from inside the Earth for heating or electricity. I'm Josiah. I can explain how it works. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is a battery"], ["A battery stores chemical energy and converts it to electrical energy. I'm Josiah. I can explain how they work or types (e.g. lithium-ion). What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is electricity"], ["Electricity is the flow of charged particles (usually electrons). It powers our homes and devices. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about electricity?"]),
    (["what is a circuit"], ["A circuit is a path for electric current—from a source (e.g. battery) through wires and components and back. I'm Josiah. What's your electricity question?"]),
    (["what is voltage"], ["Voltage is the 'push' that drives current through a circuit. It's measured in volts. I'm Josiah. Want to know more about electricity? Ask me!"]),
    (["what is current"], ["Electric current is the flow of charge through a circuit. It's measured in amperes (amps). I'm Josiah. What do you want to know about current or circuits?"]),
    (["what is resistance"], ["Resistance is how much a material opposes electric current. It's measured in ohms. I'm Josiah. I can explain Ohm's law or resistors. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is a conductor"], ["A conductor lets electric current flow easily—e.g. metals. I'm Josiah. Insulators do the opposite. What would you like to know?"]),
    (["what is an insulator"], ["An insulator resists electric current—e.g. rubber, plastic. It's used to protect and separate wires. I'm Josiah. What can I help you with?"]),
    (["what is a magnet"], ["A magnet produces a magnetic field and attracts certain metals (e.g. iron). It has north and south poles. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know about magnets?"]),
    (["what is gravity"], ["Gravity is the force that pulls objects with mass toward each other. Earth's gravity keeps us on the ground. I'm Josiah. I can explain more—what's your question?"]),
    (["what is force"], ["In physics, force is a push or pull that can change an object's motion. It's measured in newtons. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about force or motion?"]),
    (["what is energy"], ["Energy is the ability to do work—it can be kinetic (motion), potential (stored), thermal, etc. It's conserved. I'm Josiah. What's your energy question?"]),
    (["what is momentum"], ["Momentum is mass times velocity. It's conserved in a closed system. I'm Josiah. I can explain how it works. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is velocity"], ["Velocity is speed in a given direction. It's a vector. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about velocity, speed, or motion?"]),
    (["what is acceleration"], ["Acceleration is the rate of change of velocity. It can be a change in speed or direction. I'm Josiah. What's your question about motion or physics?"]),
    (["what is mass"], ["Mass is the amount of matter in an object. It's measured in kilograms. It's different from weight (which includes gravity). I'm Josiah. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is density"], ["Density is mass per unit volume. Something dense has a lot of mass in a small space. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about density or materials?"]),
    (["what is temperature"], ["Temperature measures how hot or cold something is. We use Celsius, Fahrenheit, or Kelvin. I'm Josiah. What's your temperature or heat question?"]),
    (["what is heat"], ["Heat is energy transferred between things because of a temperature difference. It flows from hot to cold. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know about heat or temperature?"]),
    (["what is light"], ["Light is electromagnetic radiation we can see. It travels in waves and at a constant speed in a vacuum. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about light?"]),
    (["what is sound"], ["Sound is vibrations that travel through a medium (air, water) as waves. We hear it when it reaches our ears. I'm Josiah. What's your sound question?"]),
    (["what is wavelength"], ["Wavelength is the distance between successive peaks of a wave. It's related to frequency and energy. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know about waves?"]),
    (["what is frequency"], ["Frequency is how many waves pass a point per second. It's measured in hertz. For sound, higher frequency means higher pitch. I'm Josiah. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is an atom"], ["An atom is the basic unit of matter. It has a nucleus (protons, neutrons) and electrons. I'm Josiah. I can explain more about atoms or elements. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is a molecule"], ["A molecule is two or more atoms bonded together. Water is H2O—two hydrogen, one oxygen. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about molecules or chemistry?"]),
    (["what is an element"], ["An element is a substance made of one type of atom. There are 118 known elements on the periodic table. I'm Josiah. What element or chemistry topic can I help with?"]),
    (["what is a compound"], ["A compound is a substance made of two or more elements in a fixed ratio. Water and salt are compounds. I'm Josiah. What's your chemistry question?"]),
    (["what is a chemical reaction"], ["A chemical reaction is when substances change into new substances—bonds break and form. I'm Josiah. I can explain types of reactions. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is ph"], ["pH measures how acidic or alkaline a solution is, from 0 (acidic) to 14 (alkaline). 7 is neutral. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about pH or acids and bases?"]),
    (["what is an acid"], ["An acid is a substance that donates protons (hydrogen ions) and has a low pH. Vinegar and lemon juice are acids. I'm Josiah. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is a base"], ["A base (alkali) accepts protons and has a high pH. Soap and baking soda are bases. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know about bases or chemistry?"]),
    (["what is oxidation"], ["Oxidation is when a substance loses electrons (e.g. rusting iron). It's often paired with reduction in redox reactions. I'm Josiah. What can I help you with?"]),
    (["what is combustion"], ["Combustion is burning—a reaction with oxygen that releases heat and light. I'm Josiah. I can explain how fire works or types of combustion. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is photosynthesis"], ["Photosynthesis is how plants use sunlight, water, and CO2 to make sugar and release oxygen. I'm Josiah. I can explain the process in more detail. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is a cell"], ["A cell is the basic unit of life. All living things are made of cells. I'm Josiah. I can explain animal vs plant cells or how they work. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is dna"], ["DNA carries genetic instructions. It's a double helix of four bases (A, T, G, C). Genes are segments of DNA. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know about DNA or genetics?"]),
    (["what is a gene"], ["A gene is a segment of DNA that codes for a protein or has another function. We inherit genes from our parents. I'm Josiah. What's your genetics question?"]),
    (["what is evolution"], ["Evolution is the change in species over time. Natural selection favours traits that help survival and reproduction. I'm Josiah. What do you want to know about evolution?"]),
    (["what is natural selection"], ["Natural selection is when organisms better suited to the environment tend to survive and reproduce more. It drives evolution. I'm Josiah. What's your question?"]),
    (["what is an ecosystem"], ["An ecosystem is a community of living things and their physical environment, all interacting. I'm Josiah. I can explain food chains, biomes, or conservation. What do you want to know?"]),
    (["what is biodiversity"], ["Biodiversity is the variety of life—species, genes, and ecosystems. It's important for healthy ecosystems. I'm Josiah. What would you like to know?"]),
